Description of female . Body (
Fig. 10
), dorsoventrally flattened, small, holotype 7.2 mm long (tip of rostrum to posterior of pleotelson), 5.5 times as long as wide, tapering towards posterior. Cephalothorax subrectangular, just longer than wide, with pronounced blunt rostrum, naked; eyelobes distinct, eyes present; anterolateral margin of sternal carapace with three or four prominent spine­like apophyses directed anteriorly. Six free pereonites; pereonite 1 shortest, about one­third as long as cephalothorax, pereonites 2 and 3 progressively longer; pereonite 5 longest, twice as long as pereonite 1 , pereonites 4 and 6 subequal, just shorter than pereonite 5 (all pereonites respectively 2.7 ; 2.2 ; 1,6; 1.3 ; 1.1 and 1.1 times as wide as long); pereonites generally laterally smoothly convex, tapering distally, naked; ventral hyposphenia present on posterior segment of cephalothorax (cheliped segment) and pereonite 1 . Pleon twice as long as pereonite 6 , of five free subequal pleonites bearing pleopods; pleonites five times as wide as long, pleonite 1 bearing continuous row of plumose setae, other pleonites without setae. Pleotelson rectangular, elongate, just less than half length of pleon, 1.4 times as long as wide, with one seta on each side and occasional pairs of dorsal setae.
